Jari Munyaradzi (right), a marathoner from Zimbabwe, who is camping at Kapsait Nike Athletics Training Camp in Elgeyo Marakwet County, the women’s World Marathon Record Holder Brigid Kosgei (second left), Kenyan-born Turkey’s athlete Yasemin Can, who runs 5,000m and 10,000m and Geoffrey Kipsang, Brigid’s pacemaker train on the Moi’s Bridge-Kachibora road in Trans Nzoia County on January 19, 2021. Jari is preparing to get a slot in their national team to the Tokyo Olympics.

 

He has been dreaming of joining athletes in Kenya for training and many of his compatriots now ask him how he managed to travel to Kenya and join the big fish. 



